00:35:45,408 --> 00:35:50,369
creative limits and then make sure the entire team is within it. It is not to say make that pixel blue not green.

653
00:35:51,210 --> 00:35:51,430
Okay.

654
00:35:53,384 --> 00:35:55,026
We didn't front load enough of our risks.

655
00:35:56,226 --> 00:35:57,427
We did a bunch of prototyping,

656
00:35:57,928 --> 00:36:01,690
but we ended up with systems that didn't work,

657
00:36:02,010 --> 00:36:05,833
with AI that was created in a vacuum

658
00:36:05,893 --> 00:36:08,635
rather than designed to work with all of our game systems

659
00:36:08,675 --> 00:36:10,216
in our story, it was a big problem.

660
00:36:11,977 --> 00:36:13,718
We ended up with some pretty compelling AI,

661
00:36:13,898 --> 00:36:17,521
but it was inconsistent, let's just say,

662
00:36:17,561 --> 00:36:20,963
in delivering the promise of human behavior.

663
00:36:23,082 --> 00:36:27,984
Oh, wait, I said this was something we did right. It was also something we did wrong. It took us

